testcase.name: when the first password is `a!1)saoYidn*/#(0nd*)` and the second one is `a!1)saoYidn*/#(0nd*)` then I expect isEqual to return `true`
when the first password is `SecretPassword2&` and the second one is `SecretPassword2&` then I expect isEqual to return `true`
when the first password is `a!1)saoYidn*/#(0nd*)` and the second one is `SecretPassword2&` then I expect isEqual to return `false`
when I create a password as `a!1)saoYidn*/#(0nd*)` then it must be equal to itself as string
when I create a password as `SecretPassword2&` then it must be equal to itself as string
when I try creating a password as `short` then I expect an error `Password must be more than 7 chars`
when I try creating a password as `aaaaaaaaaaaaaaa` then I expect an error `Password must contains at least one number, one alphabetical uppercase char, and one special char`
